    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Necessity, Not Choice</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Ben Lunine letter says Aug 20 article about lesbians transitioning into men uses language that perpetuates myth that making transition is choice rather than necessity to discover true gender identity</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>In your article, you identify real concerns of members of the lesbian community when a female-bodied person begins to transition into a man. But you use language that perpetuates one of the primary myths surrounding coming out as a transgender man -- that making this transition is a choice.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>In your article, you identify real concerns of members of the lesbian community when a female-bodied person begins to transition into a man. But you use language that perpetuates one of the primary myths surrounding coming out as a transgender man -- that making this transition is a choice.</p>
        <p>In my own transition from female to male, I made it clear to my family and friends that I wasn't a woman choosing to become a man. I was a person finally discovering my true gender identity and changing my body accordingly.</p>
        <p>Ben Lunine  San Francisco</p>
      </block>
    </body.content>
